        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="eferr9TLxHA396iQWkDf-65" value="workload-2-admin" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#b0e3e6;strokeColor=#0e8088;opacity=50;" vertex="1" parent="eferr9TLxHA396iQWkDf-14">
          <mxGeometry x="505" y="330" width="100" height="20" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="eferr9TLxHA396iQWkDf-66" value="workload-2-ro" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#b0e3e6;strokeColor=#0e8088;opacity=50;" vertex="1" parent="eferr9TLxHA396iQWkDf-14">
          <mxGeometry x="505" y="360" width="100" height="20" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="eferr9TLxHA396iQWkDf-76" value="IAM Principal Access Boundaries (PAB) functions as a resource eligibility layer within GCP which allows for carving the GCP org into restrictive boundaries.&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Fundamentally, it is applied at a certain level (folder, project, etc...) and then enforced in that every principal bind to this same level are beholden to the eligibility boundary maintained there.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Additionally, PABs are inherited. A workload&#39;s principal would inherit the org, AW, and it&#39;s own workload PAB and all three are evaluated at time of access&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#ffe6cc;strokeColor=#d79b00;opacity=60;" vertex="1" parent="eferr9TLxHA396iQWkDf-14">
          <mxGeometry x="470" y="560" width="280" height="220" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="eferr9TLxHA396iQWkDf-121" value="Provisionally, I propose a three-tier Principal Access Boundary Hierarchy:&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;org-level PAB&lt;/b&gt;: prevents exfill and permissioning for anything that&#39;s not in the org&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Assured Workloads-level PAB&lt;/b&gt;: Prevents cross-talk / permissions between MOD and HIGH environments.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;(One exception that would need to be added is the FAST core projects to allow for managing of the MOD regime)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Workload-level PAB&lt;/b&gt;: Ensures principals operating in that workload are eligible to access only resources within their workload folder.&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#ffe6cc;strokeColor=#d79b00;opacity=60;" vertex="1" parent="eferr9TLxHA396iQWkDf-14">
          <mxGeometry x="80" y="550" width="380" height="230" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="eferr9TLxHA396iQWkDf-16" value="There are three types of IAM roles:&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;- Basic:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Google recommends never using these unless necessary. These provide overarching permissions and are typically far too broad (owner, editor, viewer)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- &lt;b&gt;Pre-defined&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;These are the roles Google recommends utilizing for the majority of use cases. They are maintained by Google and include specific job domains / functional areas and conglomerate the necessary permissions to accomplish these functions&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;- Custom&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Custom roles allow picking and assigned every API level permission of a specific service to the role. These are recommended where necessary but are also cautioned against by Google (due to the amount of management overhead introduced by custom roles)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Custom roles also have quotas associated with it. Only 300 custom roles can exist per org + per project.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#ffe6cc;strokeColor=#d79b00;opacity=60;" vertex="1" parent="0mNAfT45cDVfXiYpLNkF-1">
          <mxGeometry x="-40" y="610" width="380" height="360" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="eferr9TLxHA396iQWkDf-17" value="PAB" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#e1d5e7;strokeColor=#9673a6;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontSize=12;fontColor=default;" vertex="1" parent="0mNAfT45cDVfXiYpLNkF-1">
          <mxGeometry y="150" width="50" height="30" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="eferr9TLxHA396iQWkDf-18" value="Concept" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#fff2cc;strokeColor=#d6b656;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontSize=12;" vertex="1" parent="0mNAfT45cDVfXiYpLNkF-1">
          <mxGeometry y="200" width="50" height="30" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="eferr9TLxHA396iQWkDf-19" value="Note" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#ffe6cc;strokeColor=#d79b00;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontSize=12;" vertex="1" parent="0mNAfT45cDVfXiYpLNkF-1">
          <mxGeometry y="240" width="50" height="30" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="eferr9TLxHA396iQWkDf-172" value="" style="shape=image;verticalLabelPosition=bottom;labelBackgroundColor=default;verticalAlign=top;aspect=fixed;imageAspect=0;editableCssRules=.*;image=data:image/svg+xml,;" vertex="1" parent="0mNAfT45cDVfXiYpLNkF-1">
          <mxGeometry x="310" y="1400" width="622" height="542" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
  <diagram id="qi46lAiQ8HJ4N20OCx4B" name="Self-Service Design">
    <mxGraphModel dx="1144" dy="783" grid="1" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="850" pageHeight="1100" math="0" shadow="0">
      <root>
        <mxCell id="0" />
        <mxCell id="1" parent="0" />
        <mxCell id="RnpZSZJgftnU-dQBf8mM-1" value="This platform has been designed from the beginning to function as self-service as possible (while maintaining and enforcing guard rails)&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;With this being the case, part of the approach of this platform is to provide both ready made templates for workloads, as well as a centralized self-service process for creating platform controlled resources&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#ffe6cc;strokeColor=#d79b00;opacity=60;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry width="430" height="100" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="RnpZSZJgftnU-dQBf8mM-6" value="A pull request is created that centrally gates the request of the project and allows for review by the associated team for correctness" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#f8cecc;strokeColor=#b85450;opacity=60;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="560" y="300" width="210" height="70" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
